#DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Truck hijackings have spiked in the fourth quarter. According to the rise in food costs, there are concerns that the situation could get worse. The latest crime statistics, which cover the fourth quarter of the 2021/22 financial year, indicate that truck hijackings increased by 31.4 percent. READ: Study reveals South Africans looking for cheaper food products Crime against businesses has been on the rise for a number of years. The latest statistics show that commercial crime increased by 12.7 percent. READ: Crime in SA | Two officers arrested for truck hijacking According to the Road Freight Association, investors have long complained of crime as one of the hindrances of doing business in the country. Companies are now having to spend more on private security services. The association says trucks will continue to be targeted as food inflation rises.